==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Porphyrogenitism
<hw>Por`phy*ro*gen"i*tism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>porphyro genitus</ets>, fr. Gr. <?/; <?/ purple + root of
<grk>gi`gnesqai</grk> to be born.]</ety> <def>The principle of
succession in royal families, especially among the Eastern Roman
emperors, by which a younger son, if born after the accession of his
father to the throne, was preferred to an elder son who was not so
born.</def> <rj><au>Sir T. Palgrave.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Porphyry</ent>⟦br⟧
